apiDescription: An error returned from the Sender::send or SyncSender::send function on channels.

A send operation can only fail if the receiving end of a channel is disconnected, implying that the data could never be received. The error contains the data being sent as a payload so it can be recovered.

trait implementations.name: impl<T> std::marker::Send for std::sync::mpsc::SendError<T> where T: std::marker::Send
impl<T> std::marker::Sync for std::sync::mpsc::SendError<T> where T: std::marker::Sync
